@71   = ~The most common version of the battle axe is a stout pole about four feet in length with a single-edged, trumpet-shaped blade mounted on one end. Battle axes are also called broad axes.

The dwarven smith Breagar has improved this weapon, so it won't break during a fight.

STATISTICS:

Damage: 1d8 (Slashing)
Weight: 7
Speed Factor: 7
Requirement: 10 Strength
Proficiency Type: Axe
Type: 1-handed

Not usable by:
- Thieves
- Druids
- Clerics
- Mages
- Monks~
@72   = ~ The flail is a sturdy wooden handle attached to an iron rod, a wooden rod with spikes, or a spiked iron ball. Between the handle and its implement is either a hinge or chain link. The weapon was originally used as a tool for threshing grain. 

The dwarven smith Breagar has improved this weapon, so it won't break during a fight.

STATISTICS:

Damage: 1d6 +1 (Crushing)
