- Druids
- Clerics
- Mages
- Monks~
@77   = ~One of man's earliest weapons, dating back to the most primitive of times, the first spears were simply wooden poles or sticks sharpened at one end. When man mastered metals, spearheads were made from iron and steel. Having reached this end, weaponers began experimenting with different types of spear heads, thus leading to the development of certain polearm types.

The dwarven smith Breagar has improved this weapon, so it won't break during a fight.

STATISTICS:

Damage: 1d6 (Piercing)
Weight: 5
Speed Factor: 6
Requirement: 5 Strength
