@190  = ~After Breagar and <CHARNAME> said their goodbyes, the dwarf travelled alone into the north. Even though he wanted to return to the halls of his clan, he felt that his path would lead him into another direction. Guided by Berronar's Axe, he travelled the world alone and lived through quite a few adventures, during which he affirmed himself again and again as a fighter for good. When Breagar passed on after a long fulfilled life, his remains were brought to the halls of Clan Bardormar. Only in death, the restless warrior finally found peace in the fold of his home, that he had never seen again in life.~
@191  = ~After Breagar and <CHARNAME> said their goodbyes, the dwarf traveled back to the Sword Coast to finally complete his task, to forge a ring of elements. He still had to live through many adventures, but eventually he stood at the gates of his clan to put the ring on Audhild's finger as an engagement gift. Breagar took on the position of mastersmith, after Galthur had retired, and when a few years later the banished Reggik stood before the clan's gates, he advocated for his reinstatement. Reggik and Breagar never became close friends, but both had learned to look beyond their own points of view and together worked as a perfect team to honor the clan. When Audhild passed away after a long life, Breagar made one last journey. He visited Suldanessanar, Athkatla and Baldur's Gate, and many other places he had travelled with <CHARNAME>. Eventually he reached Candlekeep. The monks were flabbergasted, when an ancient dwarf with long, white beard told them he once, travelled with the Child of Bhaal, who grew up there. To be allowed inside, he gave the library a new Book of Smithing, penned by himself. Breagar was cordially received, but when the monks tried to wake him the next day, the old dwarf laid dead in his bed. Breagar had entered Berronar's halls with a smile on his face, to spend eternity with his beloved Audhild.~
@192  = ~After Breagar and <CHARNAME> said their goodbyes, the dwarf traveled back to the Sword Coast to finally complete his task, to forge a ring of elements. He still had to live through many adventures, but eventually he stood at the gates of his clan to put the ring on Audhild's finger as an engagement gift. He was welcomed in all honors, because words of his heroic deeds had already reached the clan. Breagar took on the position of mastersmith, after Galthur had retired, and exercised it diligently for many years. When Audhild passed away after a long life, Breagar made one last journey. He visited Suldanessanar, Athkatla and Baldur's Gate, and many other places he had travelled with <CHARNAME>. Eventually he reached Candlekeep. The monks were flabbergasted, when an ancient dwarf with long, white beard told them he once, travelled with the Child of Bhaal, who grew up there. To be allowed inside, he gave the library a new Book of Smithing, penned by himself. Breagar was cordially received, but when the monks tried to wake him the next day, the old dwarf laid dead in his bed. Breagar had entered Berronar's halls with a smile on his face, to spend eternity with his beloved Audhild.~
