@10000 = ~Find the book of the dwarf

A dwarf at the Candlekeep Inn is waiting for Adam to bring him a book. Seems that idler has been getting distracted again...~
@10001 = ~ Find the book of the dwarf

Adam gave me the Tome to bring it to the dwarf.~
@10002 = ~ Find the book of the dwarf

I have sent Adam to Winthrop, so he could deliver the book. I better check, if he had arrived there.~
@10003 = ~I have found Breagar's book

Breagar, the dwarf at Winthrop's inn, calmed down and even invited me for a beer! But now he has left. I should visit the Thunderhammer Smithy in Beregost, if I ever come to that town.~
@10004 = ~I have found Breagar's book

I brought the dwarf his book and got a few coins for my troubles. What a cheap skate!~
@10005 = ~Breagar is looking for iron

The dwarf is desperately looking for some good iron. Maybe getting him some would pay off.~
@10006 = ~Breagar has his iron

The dwarf is working at Taerom's smithy. Maybe I should visit him to see how things are going.~
@10007 = ~Breagar has left

The dwarf went looking for iron by himself.~
@10008 = ~Breagar needs a priest!

I have to go to the Song of the Morning Temple and find help for Breagar as fast as possible!~
@10009 = ~Breagar's accident in the Thunderhammer Smithy 

Seems like some magical blast has torn-off Breagar's hand. Taerom has dragged him to the temple. I for myself have better things to do.~
@10010 = ~Breagar has died

I took too long, and the dwarf died of his injuries.~
@10011 = ~Breagar's accident in the Thunderhammer Smithy

The cleric Revianel has gone to the smithy to save Breagar. I should hurry to follow her.~
@10012 = ~Breagar's life was saved

The smith went on his journey. I hope things will turn out well for him.~
@10013 = ~Breagar's life was saved 

The dwarf joined us out of gratitude. Let's hope he will turn out to be a capable companion.~
@10014 = ~A giant in the Cloud Peaks?

A strange dwarf, who called herself a messenger of Berronar, gave Breagar a task. A giant roaming the Cloud Peaks has defiled a temple. We should kill the giant and regain three artifacts that he has stolen.~
@10015 = ~ A giant in the Cloud Peaks

Breagar has left the group, to complete the task the dwarven gods have given him by himself.~
@10016 = ~A giant in the Cloud Peaks!

There really was a giant called Yrrymyr in the Cloud Peaks! The fight was easier than expected, as the giant was tired after a long journey. Our reward wasn't bad at all: Breagar's was replaced with the arm of a silver golem, and he was given the sacred axe of Berronar as a reward. Besides, the giant had quite a few gold coins on him...~
@10017 = ~Dark Prophecy

The strange dwarf, who Breagar called a messenger of Berronar, had a few things to tell me. It seems the dwarven gods are interested in my path. Breagar was chosen, to accompany me, and I think that a brave fighter like him can be of use. Time will tell what the prophecy was about: Out of the ash of the old gods, new life will arise...~
@10018 = ~Taerom needs help: Revianel has disappeared

The priestess who saved Breagar's life has disappeared on a mission for the temple, and Taerom needs our help. Seems like he took her disappearance personally...~
@10019 = ~ Revianel has disappeared – we have to talk to Tobin

The priest who was out on a mission with Revianel should be at the temple vestibule.~
@10020 = ~ Revianel has disappeared

I decided not to look for the priestess. The fate of the Sword Coast is more important than the life of one woman.~
@10021 = ~The Evil under the graveyard - Tobin leads the way

The priest will be our guide and lead us to the graveyard, so we can investigate there.~
@10022 = ~We will meet Revianel at the entrance of the graveyard

The priestess wants to travel back together with Tobin.~
@10023 = ~The cleric Revianel was saved

Revianel and Taerom went back to the temple. Breagar is glad to have paid back his debts in parts. It feels great to have done something good.~
@10024 = ~Grothir at the Splurging Sturgeon is looking for a contract

Grothir, a dwarf of Breagar's clan, signed an ill-conceived contract with the Iron Throne. He would be thankful, if we could go there and get the contract back.~
@10025 = ~Grothir has the contract

Clan Bardormar won't sign any more contracts with the Iron Throne any time soon.~
@10026 = ~Berronar's Axe was stolen

Seems like our captor didn't just take my equipment. Breagar's beloved silver axe, blessed by the dwarven goddess Berronar, was stolen. If we want it back, we should look for it as soon as possible... once we are out of this dungeon.~
@10027 = ~Do the Shadow Thieves know something about Berronar's Axe?

A hooded dwarf approached Breagar and suggested the Shadow Thieves might know something about Berronar's Axe. We should ask around.~
@10028 = ~Do the Shadow Thieves know something about Berronar's Axe?

The fence of the Shadow Thieves promised she would ask around for a fee. I should return, once I have enough to make her a good offer.~
@10029 = ~Do the Shadow Thieves know something about Berronar's Axe?

Instead of gold, the fence might accept an amulet of the Harpers as payment for information.~
@10030 = ~Do the Shadow Thieves know something about Berronar's Axe?

I could barely hold back Breagar, not to start a private war with the Shadow Thieves. At the end the fence agreed to ask around. A messenger will find us, should something turn up.~
@10031 = ~Berronar's Axe: A lead at the promenade

Seems like a gnome called Arnie was involved in the theft. He is said to be somewhere at the promenade.~
@10032 = ~Berronar's Axe: The tower of Anstinus

Arnie had a letter, signed by Reggik. He was asked to come to the Tower of Anstinus. We should find out more there, and if anyone knows where to find that tower, it's Cromwell.~
@10033 = ~Berronar's Axe: The tower of Anstinus

If Breagar is right, we should find that tower in the Troll Mountains.~
@10034 = ~Berronar's Axe: The tower of Anstinus

We were able to enter the tower without problems. The axe must be close...~
@10035 = ~Tower of Anstinus: The Potion of Green Fire

The great Anstinus, or at least, what was left of him, asked us to create the Potion of Green Fire. The ingredients should all be somewhere in the tower...~
@10036 = ~Tower of Anstinus: The Potion of Green Fire

We have released the tower of Anstinus and gained the keystone to the basement.~
@10037 = ~Berronar's Axe: Keystone of Anstinus

We have gained the keystone, Reggik gave to the ghost of Anstinus for safe-keeping. It should open the way to the basement.~
@10038 = ~Bork and Ellie

A half-orc, who lurked in front of the Tower of Anstinus, was looking for someone called Ellie... well, he's no longer looking for her.~
@10039 = ~Bork and Ellie

I agreed to help the half-orc Bork in his search for Ellie. She should be somewhere in the Tower of Anstinus.~
@10040 = ~Elasia the Ranger

In the tower of Anstinus I encountered Elasia, who attacked me. I defended myself.~
@10041 = ~Bork and Ellie

The half-orc Bork has forced the elf Elasia into some kind of marriage. Elasia wants to be free of him, without killing Bork... How could I possibly help her?~
@10042 = ~Bork and Ellie

I have brought Bork and Ellie together – in the afterlife.~
@10043 = ~Bork and Ellie

I have made Elasia remember her oath. As a ranger she is bound to always speak the truth. She has returned to Bork to live at his side.~
@10044 = ~Bork and Ellie

I have turned Elasia invisible and helped her sneak by Bork. Maybe I should talk to the half-orc now.~
@10045 = ~Bork and Ellie

Elasia is hiding in tower of Anstinus and wants to sneak by Bork. A Potion of Invisibility or a spell would help her.~
@10046 = ~Bork and Ellie

Now that Bork is dead, the elf Elasia can continue her journey.~
@10047 = ~Breagar in Saradush

Breagar mentioned, that there are dwarves in Saradush, who are in need of Berronar's support. We should look around.~
@10048 = ~Breagar's text fragments

Breagar has found fragments of a book about Berronar's Axe and wants to restore it, but doesn't know how. Visiting a temple of Oghma, god of wisdom, might be advisable.~

@10049 = ~Breagar's text fragments

We found the scribe Wallisek in the temple of Oghma, who could restore the book for Breagar.~

@10050 = ~Breagar's text fragments

We found the scribe Wallisek in the temple of Oghma, who could restore the book for Breagar. Unfortunately we don't have all the fragments yet. We have to find them to restore the book.~

@10051 = ~Breagar's text fragments

The monk Wallisek estimates, that there are three fragments.~

@10052 = ~Breagar's text fragments

The monk Wallisek assumes, that we might find the fragments with dwarves or people specializing in weapon crafting.~

@10053 = ~Breagar's text fragments

The monk Wallisek is restoring the book about Berronar's Axe. We should come back in a few days, to see the results.~

@10054 = ~Breagar's text fragments

The Book about Berronar's Axe has been restored!~

@10055 = ~The Tower of Anstinus is under siege

The silver dwarf appeared again and informed Breagar that the tower of Anstinus was in danger. Without hesitation, we agreed to investigate. The silver dwarf was pleased and immediately teleported us there. But what now? Should we secure the outside or take a look inside?~

/* Forres and Reggik, Duergar can stay */
@10056 = ~The Tower of Anstinus is under siege

We followed the sounds of battle and found Forres and Reggik fighting off spiders. After dealing with them, they told us that drow and other scum had broken through the corridors below the tower. Breagar let me decide, how to handle the situation. We persuaded Breagar to help them reclaim the tower.~

